<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-9034864/R-HSA-9034864>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> , <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0046579> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "Upon activation by NTF3 (NT-3), the receptor tyrosine kinase NTRK3 (TRKC) triggers RAS signaling through adaptor proteins SHC1 and GRB2 (Marsh and Palfrey 1996, Gunn-Moore et al. 1997, Yuen and Mobley 1999). ERK activation downstream of NTRK3 may increase cell motility through WAVE. The mechanism is not known (Gromnitza et al. 2018)." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Activated NTRK3 signals through RAS" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "Reviewed: Tsoulfas, Pantelis, 2018-05-09" , "Authored: Orlic-Milacic, Marija, 2018-01-02" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Orlic-Milacic, Marija, 2018-05-09" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date>
